# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  PURPOSE ▸ Ensure every generated file carries a consistent, Swiss-grid,
#            cyber-punk comment header + placeholder block.
#
#  RULES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  1.  Header always at top-of-file. Use language-native comment tokens.
#  2.  Box layout:
#        • Outer border uses heavy box-drawing glyphs (╔ ═ ╗ ║ ╚).
#        • Title line in ALL-CAPS, mono-aligned left; pad with "░".
#        • Blank canvas inside for future content (spaces only, no filler char).
#  3.  After box, append WHAT / WHY / HOW trio — bulleted with "•".
#  4.  Keep total width **72 chars** (ideal for side-by-side diff).
#  5.  Use monospace alignment; pad with single spaces (␠) only.
#  6.  Colour words (if supported) NEVER hard-coded in source; just glyphs.
#  7.  Inline comments later in file → prefix with "⟢" (arrow-dot) for quick scan.
#  8.  Never exceed ~50% comment density in code files.
#  9.  Markdown docs use HTML comments with same grid.
# 10. Glossary keywords → UPPER-SNAKE (CARET, DIFF, ACTIVE_REGION) on first mention.
#
#  TEMPLATES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  • TypeScript / JS / Swift / Java / Kotlin
#    ---------------------------------------------------------
